### 3. Visual Branding Tips
To make your repository stand out like a real product:

1.  **Add a Banner:** Create a simple 1280x640 image with the "Hello Astha" logo and place it at the very top of your README.
2.  **Use Shields.io:** Use the badges at the top of the README (I included some in the template) to show your tech stack.[[1](https://www.google.com/url?sa=E&q=https%3A%2F%2Fvertexaisearch.cloud.google.com%2Fgrounding-api-redirect%2FAUZIYQGiCuNjmOWjdOLCFCrM4rvmk0hWIO-nOIE3m-7Oo5Iu3cDctECy8HpYvKqoDjw3eyALTa7quWRryabXVEU8urukkUU4_VGJdwFkiLkgYKA0-rfTuCu4JuRKeZJ39-qiXZB0jKc6Xw%3D%3D)]
3.  **Create a Demo GIF:** Use a tool like **ScreenToGif** to record yourself using the app. Put that GIF in the "Screenshots" section. It's much more impressive than static images.
4.  **Social Preview:** Go to your GitHub Repository **Settings** -> **General** -> **Social preview** and upload your logo. This is the image people see when you share the link on social media.

### 4. Important Files to Include
*   **`.gitignore`**: Make sure it includes `node_modules` and `.env`. You don't want to leak your database password!
*   **`LICENSE`**: Go to GitHub -> Add File -> Create New File -> Type "LICENSE".[[1](https://www.google.com/url?sa=E&q=https%3A%2F%2Fvertexaisearch.cloud.google.com%2Fgrounding-api-redirect%2FAUZIYQGiCuNjmOWjdOLCFCrM4rvmk0hWIO-nOIE3m-7Oo5Iu3cDctECy8HpYvKqoDjw3eyALTa7quWRryabXVEU8urukkUU4_VGJdwFkiLkgYKA0-rfTuCu4JuRKeZJ39-qiXZB0jKc6Xw%3D%3D)] Choose the **MIT License**—it's standard for projects like this.
